<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title><%= pageTitle %></title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:wght@500;600;700&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700;800&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <link
      href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"
      rel="stylesheet"
      integrity="sha384-QWTKZyjpPEjISv5WaRU9OFeRpok6YctnYmDr5pNlyT2bRjXh0JMhjY6hW+ALEwIH"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg sticky-top navbar-shell">
        <div class="container nav-shell-inner">
          <button
            class="navbar-toggler"
            type="button"
            data-bs-toggle="collapse"
            data-bs-target="#mainNav"
            aria-controls="mainNav"
            aria-expanded="false"
            aria-label="Toggle navigation"
          >
            <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
          </button>
          <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="mainNav">
            <ul class="navbar-nav nav-center">
              <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/">Home</a></li>
              <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link active" href="/about">About</a></li>
              <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/services">Services</a></li>
              <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/process">Work</a></li>
              <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/contact">Contact</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main>
      <section class="page-top-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="section-heading text-center" data-reveal="up">
            <p class="section-tag">About</p>
            <h1>About Cognifyz Solutions</h1>
            <p>
              A clean business-style about page with company details and animated stats.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row g-5 align-items-center about-layout">
            <div class="col-lg-6" data-reveal="up">
              <div class="about-story-panel">
                <p class="eyebrow-text">Our story</p>
                <h2 class="h1 about-main-title">Who we are</h2>
                <p>
                  Cognifyz Solutions is presented as a frontend-focused digital company
                  that helps businesses build responsive websites and clean user interfaces.
                </p>
                <p>
                  The goal is to create pages that feel modern and polished while staying
                  practical for real businesses, product teams, and internship-level delivery.
                </p>
                <ul class="content-list about-points">
                  <% aboutHighlights.forEach((item) => { %>
                    <li><%= item %></li>
                  <% }) %>
                </ul>
                <div class="about-actions">
                  <a href="/services" class="btn btn-primary">View Services</a>
                  <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-outline-primary">Talk to Our Team</a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-lg-6" data-reveal="up">
              <div class="about-visual-card">
                <div class="about-floating-badge float-slow">UI planning + delivery</div>
                <div class="about-dashboard-panel">
                  <div class="dashboard-window">
                    <div class="dashboard-bar"></div>
                    <div class="dashboard-grid">
                      <div class="dashboard-block dashboard-block-large"></div>
                      <div class="dashboard-block"></div>
                      <div class="dashboard-block"></div>
                      <div class="dashboard-block dashboard-block-accent"></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-mini-card about-mini-card-left float-soft">
                  <span class="mini-card-icon">01</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>Structured workflow</strong>
                    <p class="mb-0">Planning, design review, and polished frontend delivery.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="about-mini-card about-mini-card-right float-slow">
                  <span class="mini-card-icon">02</span>
                  <div>
                    <strong>User-first interface</strong>
                    <p class="mb-0">Readable layouts, responsive sections, and clean handoff.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-detail-section mt-5" data-reveal="up">
            <div class="row g-5 align-items-start">
              <div class="col-lg-5">
                <div class="about-copy-block">
                  <p class="eyebrow-text">How we work</p>
                  <h3 class="h2">A frontend process that stays clear from start to finish</h3>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    We prefer readable structure, strong section flow, and visual decisions
                    that help businesses explain what they offer without cluttering the page.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-lg-7">
                <div class="about-highlight-list">
                  <div class="about-highlight-item">
                    <h4>Clear communication</h4>
                    <p>
                      Project discussions stay simple and direct so clients can quickly
                      understand progress, updates, and next steps.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="about-highlight-item">
                    <h4>Build with purpose</h4>
                    <p>
                      Every section is shaped around readability, trust, and user action
                      instead of decorative elements that add noise.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="about-highlight-item">
                    <h4>Responsive by default</h4>
                    <p>
                      Layouts are planned for desktop, tablet, and mobile from the start
                      so the design stays balanced on every screen size.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-wide-section" data-reveal="up">
            <div class="row g-5 align-items-start">
              <div class="col-lg-4">
                <div class="about-section-intro">
                  <p class="eyebrow-text">What clients notice</p>
                  <h3 class="h2">The page should feel complete before it feels decorative</h3>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-lg-8">
                <div class="about-reading-flow">
                  <div class="about-reading-item">
                    <span>01</span>
                    <div>
                      <h4>Simple structure</h4>
                      <p>
                        Pages are arranged so users always know what the business does,
                        what value it offers, and where to act next.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="about-reading-item">
                    <span>02</span>
                    <div>
                      <h4>Better line-up</h4>
                      <p>
                        Sections are aligned with a consistent reading rhythm so the page
                        feels intentional instead of randomly stacked.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                  <div class="about-reading-item">
                    <span>03</span>
                    <div>
                      <h4>Useful visuals</h4>
                      <p>
                        Animation and 3D depth are kept subtle so the design supports trust
                        and clarity rather than distracting the user.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-wide-section about-experience-section" data-reveal="up">
            <div class="row g-5 align-items-start">
              <div class="col-lg-6">
                <div class="about-section-intro">
                  <p class="eyebrow-text">Experience philosophy</p>
                  <h3 class="h2">Why this frontend style works for real business pages</h3>
                  <p>
                    A strong business site is not only about colors or motion. It needs
                    clear section hierarchy, fast understanding, and content that can be
                    scanned easily by first-time visitors.
                  </p>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    That is why the focus stays on structure, spacing, messaging, and
                    responsive behavior before decorative UI decisions.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-lg-6">
                <div class="about-column-list">
                  <div class="about-column-item">
                    <h4>Business clarity</h4>
                    <p>
                      Visitors should quickly understand the offer, the workflow, and how
                      the service solves a real problem.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="about-column-item">
                    <h4>Visual discipline</h4>
                    <p>
                      Layout rhythm, margins, and typography should stay consistent from
                      the top of the page to the footer.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                  <div class="about-column-item">
                    <h4>Responsive confidence</h4>
                    <p>
                      Mobile and tablet views should feel planned, not reduced versions of
                      the desktop screen.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-wide-section" data-reveal="up">
            <div class="about-journey-strip">
              <div class="about-journey-head">
                <p class="eyebrow-text">Working model</p>
                <h3 class="h2">From first conversation to final delivery</h3>
              </div>
              <div class="about-journey-list">
                <div class="about-journey-item">
                  <strong>Discover</strong>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Understand business goals, audience expectations, and the structure each
                    page needs before visual work starts.
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="about-journey-item">
                  <strong>Design</strong>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Build a clean interface direction with aligned sections, readable text,
                    and visuals that strengthen the message.
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="about-journey-item">
                  <strong>Deliver</strong>
                  <p class="mb-0">
                    Refine the frontend for responsiveness, smoother interaction, and a
                    final presentation that feels complete.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="about-cta-band" data-reveal="up">
            <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
              <div class="col-lg-8">
                <p class="eyebrow-text">Next step</p>
                <h3 class="h2 mb-2">Need a cleaner and more impressive frontend presence?</h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  The same structure-first approach can be used for service websites,
                  landing pages, and product-facing frontend projects.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="col-lg-4 text-lg-end">
                <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary">Start the discussion</a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <div class="container footer-row">
        <div>
          <strong>Cognifyz Solutions</strong>
          <p class="mb-0">Frontend design and development for structured web projects.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="footer-links">
          <a href="/">Home</a>
          <a href="/services">Services</a>
          <a href="/process">Work</a>
          <a href="/contact">Contact</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </footer>

    <script
      src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js"
      integrity="sha384-YvpcrYf0tY3lHB60NNkmXc5s9fDVZLESaAA55NDzOxhy9GkcIdslK1eN7N6jIeHz"
      crossorigin="anonymous"
    ></script>
    <script src="/app.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
